values:
it's been quite some time since i've written sumthin. i've just been kinda busy lately it seems like. except at nights when there's nothing to do. i just do cheerleading all the time. i can't wait till March-its my birthday and i'll just have a blast and yeah. i dunno what to say. my life has been crazy these past few months. not much to say about it though. been having a rough time dealing with everyone though. i wish i had a boyfriend at this point, i'm very much ready for one. i have someone in mind, that no one knows about, and i think he might like me...so yeah, we'll just let it all work itself out!! but yeah, i'll ttyl homies!! i'm out!

~*!Danielle Elise

wow--a lot of stuff has happened ever since i've written. well, i'll touch the major points. toward the end of june, there was a last tuesday concert in warren, allura told me about it, so i went. i took tammy and jamie with me, it was a good time. on the fourth of July i had an AWESOME time! first i went to the parade with Jamie-and i saw a BUNCH of time friends there, like, almost all of my Warren friends-it was good. then that night i went to the fireworks with Tammy and we met up with Jamie later on. it was great. nothing really happened until the end of July-Sherry left for Texas. it sucked-seriously. then fair week came-oh my gosh that was a BLAST!! every day i ended up hanging out with Kasi then almost every day i would end up hanging out with a guy. lol. but it was all good. well, the last night i was kinda ticked off becuz a bunch of my "friends" said that they would love to hang out with me and when they had the chance-they acted like they didn't want to, oh well. the band camp came, blah, then exhibition. after exhibition my friends had a party so, i went up to that. school started. then i got a boyfriend. he's a senior. but, a week and a half later, he broke up with me. he "couldn't keep his priorites straight with a girlfriend"-oh well. homecoming was last weekend. oh my gosh, it was AWESOME!! i loved it!! the dance ROCKED!! but, i better get goin.

well, on Friday, after school, Club Crossroads made lunch for the teachers. then after that we went over to the Joy Hall for a movie party. We watched Back to the Future and ate pizza. then i left there and went to graduation. we had to have graduation inside-man it was hot in there!! but then after graduation i stood around with Sara-i always have a good time with that gurl. then after that Britney picked me up and took me out to Ashley's house. Man, we had SOO much fun!! it was our Great Group of Six-Danni, Ashley Wilcox, Ashley Wilson, Cassie, Amber, and Ashley Wilson. we pitched a tent so we could sleep outside-well, we tried to anywayz! then Ashley's dad came home and redid it. we went swimming at like 10 at night. we were all really hyper. then we went up and played DDR. then after that Ashley's mom made us a fire and we made smores. then we went to the tent and stayed up and talked and took picutres. Ashley's digital camera can take pictures when it's pitch dark out and it'll look like it's day. we had a wondeful "Circle" time where we asked questions and all of us answered them. then we got up in the mornin at like 8. we all got breakfast and Cassie left. then Ashley M. and W. left. then the 3 of us went swimming. then we played some more DDR. then Amber left and me and Ashley got some lunch. then we watched Taxi-then my dad came and got me. it was like 2 by then. then he took me home and then we went over to his friend Andy's house and we went swimming. then we came back home and i washed my hair then we went out to dinner. then after that we went out to Spring Creek and my dad golfed while i drove the golf cart. then we came home and i played DDR cuz Ashley is lettin me borrow it. i had a great weekend. i seriously did. today i might be goin up to the pool-it all matter on whether Jamie goes up. PEACE OUT & ROCK ON!!!

man, today was my last full day of being an "ankle biter" or "midget" as the seniors would say-lol. it went by SOOOO fast it wasn't even funny. but, i had a BLAST with me and my friends. man, we had SO much fun. well, Cassie brought in her digital camera and got a BUNCH of picutres of me-lol. she should be sending them to me soon. but anywayz, i just talked to my friends all day-that's all we did. Cassie got a good pic of me and Jayda being really hyper-it's funny. i convinced Mr. Reynolds to take our class out to the courtyard. lol. me and Jayda were daning around and acting like complete idiots-oh well, like my saying "it's better to look like an idiot with someone else rather than look like an idiot by yourself". i am going to school tomorrow, i just don't wanna go to bed quite yet. i really don't know why though. oh well. i'm just SOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOO glad that school is over. Tomorrow after graduation i'm heading up to Ashley Wilcox's house. it's gonna be me, Ashley M., Ashley Wilson, Amber and Cassie all up at Ashley Wilcox's house. it's really confusing when you have 3 people with the same name in the same place-lol. well, i guess i got used to it after sitting with them at lunch. we got a good pic of Ashley, we had to like HOLD her down to get the one picutre of her-it's funny. i can't wait to see it. i'm holding her one arm in the pic. i had a good last full day of school-i really did. oh, and me and my lil cuz Zach had fun during computer messing with the photo editor on the comps doin stuff to the picutres that i had saved on my account. like, i had the pic of me and Andrew on there, and he like smugged his face-it was funny. but, i better get goin. PEACE OUT AND ROCK ON!!!!!!!!!!!!! ~^*Danni Elise

well, not much has been going on lately. um, i joined myspace!! www.myspace.com/perfect_ray_of_sunshine if y'all wanna see it!! um, jazz concert tomorrow! so totally nervous like none other, seriously. last day for LEC for the year tomorrow-man, it's gonna be weird. only 6 and a half more days left!! thank GOD!!! i'm so sick of school-seriously, i just want the year to be over with. next year's gonna be better-i can feel it. going to Chicago is gonna ROCK!! get me as far away from here as long as i possibly can. but yeah, not much going on here! just finals coming up and all that crap. math final tomorrow-haha i get outta it-more time to study. i don't know when the rest of my finals are, oh well. but, i'm goin to the Fairmont for chicken wings then going over to Fuel. PEACE OUT!! ~^*Danni Elise

man, i'm home and i'm sad, and yet happy at the same time. i'm sad cuz i had to leave the OBX, but i'm happy cuz i'm home. wow-on Tuesday night if i remember correctly Tessa B. came to the beach. after she got there, i wasn't bored. we had A LOT of fun!! man, one of the nights we went crabbin, and we only found one sand crab and we found a fish head and a lobster leg-only the leg was there, it was weird. and we went swimming at like 2 in the morning the other day, it was fun!! umm....the drive home was long too. i should be going to Jamie's house tonight. she needs to call me back-when i called her about 5 minutes ago she wasn't home-i wonder where she is. oh well! leaving that beach was a hard thing man, it really was. i could seriously live there if i really wanted to. but, this is my home, and nothin really compares to it. i missed everyone, i really did. it was weird not bein able to talk to everyone every day.

wow, sittin here at the OBX watchin people play bull crap. it's interesting. hmm..today was a sucky day..the weather sucked..i went shoppin with my parents and bought a shirt, shorts, necklace, and keychain. i went swimmin in the pool cuz it's heated and everythang. i took a nap...wow...today was really boring. yesterday was like the best day ever-seriously. but, yeah, i better be heading, i love you all and i'll see ya when i get home!!! PEACE OUT!! ~^*Danni Elise

hey y'all!! just thought i'd give a quick update!! well, OBX is freakin AWESOME!!! i love it here!! i SOO wanna move here! i don't wanna watch tv right now and it's starting to get cold out so, i thought i'd get on here for a lil bit. i'm so glad to be away from Skintown. there's just too much freakin crap i needed to get away from. i know, i know, it's not good to run away from stuff. but, right now, it seemed like the only option at this point. but, the freakin house that we're staying in is BEAUTIFUL!!!!!!!!! it's SOO awesome, there's a theater, hot tub, pool, comp (obviously), a tiki bar...it just goes on and on. the house is ocean front, and i can see the ocean if i look to my right..as i am typing right now. man, i so love the beach, i seriously do. hmmm...the drive here was LONG!! and when i mean LONG, i mean SO FREAKIN LONG I COULD OF READ A WHOLE HARRY POTTER BOOK IN THAT TIME!!! but, it was SO worth it. but yeah, i'm gonna go head out and watch some MTV in the theatre..haha!! lol. PEACE OUT!! ~^*Danni Elise

well, only 2 more hours until i leave for the Outer Banks!! i'm SOO excited!! i'm not goin to sleep until we leave. well, i might, who knows. i just need some time away from good ol' Skintown! well, i'll probably end up callin most of you people who read these...so, yeah. I hope y'all miss me while i'm gone! lol. i'm so excited i'm going to the beach again. i'm gonna watch the sun rise and everything! there's too many people going to the beach this year. i mean, there's A LOT of people going-40 sum in one house! i mean, i love being around people it's just that, that's too many for one house. oh well, nuttin i can do about it. i'm just happy that i get to go! hmm..went to the middle school dance tonight. it was fun. i've been to better dances-way better dances. hmmm...not much to talk about anymore so, i'm outta here! PEACE OUT! ~^*Danni Elise

well, today was cheerleading try-outs. man, it was CRAZY! i did my best! well, i wast he 2nd to last person to go! well, then they came out of the gym and posted it. i saw my name...but it was under "Alternate". well, i beat all the other 8th graders who tried out and a few other girls. I'm the first and only alternate the Holly (the coach) chose to take. so, i'm just hoping someone quits. OR, if someone gets hurt, i take their place, but i really don't want that to happen. Amber said she would quit so that i could take her place, but i told her no. She didn't even wanna try out for basketball, its just the fact that Holly said that she would need her next year. like i said, i REALLY hope that someone quits, i really do. 2 MORE DAYS!!!!!!!!!

well, what can i say?? not much is going on. okay, this week, A LOT is going on!! We found out our marching band theme for this year's marching season. It's like this Spanish Dance type theme-named "El Baile". I'm still figuring out how to pronounce it right, cuz of what most people know about me, i can't pronounce words very well. and today is the beginning of cheerleading try outs. man, i'm SO nervous!!!!!! i did a toe touch in my living room for Britney and Amber last night and Amber said that it was pretty good, i just needed to work on my landing. and i know that if it was really bad, Amber would have told me. Well, today and tomorrow are just the practices. and then Thursday is the offical try outs. Then, today, after cheerleading, i have a National Honor Society thingy mo-bober to go to. man, i'm so busy this week. me and Tammy went up to Wal Mart to get our pictures developed yesterday. then i came home and scanned a bunch of pictures-17 total-and i saved them on the computer. if you want any sent to you, just tell me and i will!! but yeah, i better be heading out, PEACE OUT! ~^*Danielle Elise

Well, it's Sunday. I just got outta the shower. On Friday, after school, me and Jayda went over to the Galley while Morgan had track practice and Kasi went over to the middle school. Me and Jay waited for Kasi at the Galley. I ordered 2 pizza balls and they got one pizza ball each. Then we went over to the high school. We sat there with Morgan cuz her practice was optional so, we were allowed to be there. Then they had the elementary track meet. man, those little kids are SOOO cute!! me, Kasi, and Jayda helped with the consession stand, even though we didn't have to, we had nothin else to do, other than watch all the little kids. After the track meet we went over to TJs and got The Ring, Ghost Ship, Coyote Ugly, Barber Shop, and crap..i don't remember the other movie that we got-oh well, it ain't that important. Then Kasi's dad picked us up at Quality and we went out to her house. We watched The Ring, Coyote Ugly, and the movie that i can't remember what its name is! Then we watched a bunch of home movies that Kasi and a bunch of other people made. We didn't go to bed until like 4.

Yesterday we didn't get up until 11. We got up and thought about what we could do for a home video of our own. So, we made a home video, man, i had fun makin it!! i haven't seen it yet-Kasi's makin me a copy of it. She said it was funny. Then Jayda's mom came and picked us up. Then around 6:30 Jill picked me up and we went to Otterbien for a youth ralley thingy. I thought it was really kewl. The guys that did it from Teen Challenge were really kewl!! Then we came home.

I had a busy weekend. It was good though. I really needed to get outta the house though. Only 6 more days until i leave!!!!!!

the concert went awesome! if you didn't go-why not?? it was REALLY awesome! me and Danielle Fohrd got the "Outstanding 8th grader(s)" award! now i'm gonna have my name plaqued on the band room wall FOREVER!!!! man, i can't wait until my Senior year! i know i say that now, but, i know once i leave Youngsville, i'm gonna miss it SO much.

um...my solos went AWESOME, like always! okay..all who know about the Corry Competition 2004..shut up. that was NOT my fault! my glove got stuck somehow in my sax and i messed up. and all who were there-you know how upset i was about it.

hmmm...just band brings back so many flippin memories. both good and bad. good-championships, INDY, the games, the competitions...it goes on and on. bad-band camp, practices seeming like they were 5 days a week, James tellin Hoss to put me unconscience but we won't talk about that!

wow..i'm really hyper! Bre made me hyper!! i can't believe her!! lol! i can't wait until next year! i get to ride the band bus with her!! yay! but i won't be on the same bus as Jerry. oh well, it'll be okay.

wow. not much has happened the past few days. Sunday for Mother's Day we went out to Grandma Cerrie's house. man, i was bored. but that's okay. i got a REALLY good pic of me on Britney's digital camera by the creek by my grandma's house. i'll post it on here asap!

Monday, absolutely nothing happened. Today, i had to go to the middle school for band. i got to see all my teachers from last year! i never realized how much i missed the middle school until today. i feel tall in that building! the ceilings are so much lower over there than what i remember from last year. LOL

and then after school we had band practice. cuz our concert is tomorrow! if you can-you should come!!!!

Here's a picture from Harry Potter and the Goblet of Fire-coming out November 18, 2005!! I SOOOO can't wait!! Even though the wonderful trio looks really sad-Rupert Grint (Ron) looks REALLY hott! When i'm gonna be watching the movie, i'm probably gonna be sittin there practically drooling! lol!

Anywayayz, just sittin here in English class watching music videos with Eric on his computer. He's gonna be gone all next week. I'm not gonna have anyone to talk to when we're in the computer lab for english! i love updating during school. i dunno why-it gives me sumthin to do, i guess.

Hm..too much crap going on. i seriously can't wait to go to the OBX-only 15 more days! Goin to the boy's baseball game after school today, cuz i have nothing else better to do. I'm going with Tammy cuz if i go with Jayda she's gonna be with Andy and i'll feel like a flippin' third wheel-and i HATE that!

intersting day up at the LEC yesterday. oh man, Andrew didn't go-don't ask me why. Adam wasn't there cuz Andrew wasn't. Oh well. but, in our digital video class we needed them to do sum stuff for our movie. But we only have 3 more weeks of goin up there. We have an awesome time on the bus on the way there. on my goodness. Ashley, Amber, Kasi, Brenton, Zach, and I have a BLAST! i think we have more fun on the way there than the rest of the day! it's great! but like Amber will SLAM her face up to the back window when we stop if there is a car behind us. oh my, my eyes almost started watering i was laughin so hard.

yay! i got my internet back!! okay, it was only gone for 2 days but, still! i had nothing to do here at home! there's like never anything to do here except get on the computer!!! but yeah, Dad and Amber are in Erie right now or on their way home from gettin Britney. Jamie's here with me. i'm really bored. we went on a walk with Princess a lil while ago!!! now there's nothing to do...so, we're on here. well, that's all for now folks! lol. oh my....

well, at home, my internet is messed up so, the only time i'll be able to talk to do anything with the internet is here at school. if ya wanna talk to me, you're best bet is to call me. if ya don't know the number, it's the only Cerrie in the Warren county phone book! but yeah, not much happened last night, did jazz band, went home, watched ONE TREE HILL! man, it rocked! I almost cried though!!!!! It was SO sad! one of the main characters got into a car accident!! i hope the guy lives though!

sorry guys this is short-it HAS to be today!

well, Ashley's here today!!! yay!! well, school sucked MAJORLY, worse than other days.

Everyone here is trying their best to cheer me up. It works for about 5 minutes, then i just go back to being sad. It's hard not to think about everything that happened yesterday. Everything has just sucked after school yesterday to right now. All of my friends keep trying to make me laugh and smile and they tell me that they love me. It really helps to know that they love me. Last night Jason was the main person that got me through the night. He kept tellin me a lot of comforting stuff. He's a great friend! I love ya Jason! But, really not much has happened today. Let's see-went to home ec, math test, got a book from the library for notetaking, almost fell asleep in lunch, finished my test for science, watched Anne Frank in english, played in band, quiz in social studies, then doing cartoons in computer.

wow...what can i say?? Andrew broke up with me. i had the best thing that ever happened to me and it slipped outta my own hands. i don't even know what to say about it. i thought everything was great between us. i guess i was wrong. i just feel so stupid. i love him so much..i just wish he loved me back. oh well, what can i do?? there really isn't anything i CAN do. i'm just not gonna be the HAPPY person i normally am for a LONG time-i can tell you that right now.

ASHLEY'S NOT HERE!! I am SOOO sad!! i miss her! not really. but i'm bored cuz she's not here!! but, this day has been really boring. nothing has happened today. Andrew didn't call me last night-stupid idiot (just kidding hun!). doing a stupid web quest thingy against my will. i hate web quests-they're SOO dumb and they have NOOOO point to them!!!! grrr.

but anywayz, not much is going on this week. i don't know if i'm going to youth group tomorrow. i really have no idea. Andrew was supposed to call me-but he never did!!!

Britney comes home on Friday!! yay! but i don't get to go up to Erie to go get her cuz there won't be enough room to take either me or Amber. that's okay, i guess.

Great time at the Famine, really! On Friday at noon the famine started and we had to be at the Joy Hall. We had to get signed in and give Jill everything and all that good stuff. Then we did a game and went out and did a food drive. Then when we were done we went over to the EUM church. then we went back over to the Joy Hall, got our stuff, and then headed out for Corry. Then we got to the Salvation Army. They had a bowling alley and everything! it was really kewl! we did a lot of things. discussions, devotions, games, we got free time, juice breaks, all that good stuff. I got to play PS2 on a projection screen-oh man it was kewl! and at the end of the night we watched Incredicbles and then everyone went to bed.

Today was REALLY tiring. Joe Reed kept bring up food and it was makin me mad cuz i didn't wanna think about eating. i was still kinda sick and when you don't eat when you're sick-you're REALLY tired!!!anyways, today-when we were supposed to leave the Salvation Army to go back to the Joy Hall to break our fast, we got in the big 15 passenger van and all the other vehicles left-and the van wouldn't start!!!!!!!!!!! it was like 4:45 when everyone else left. so, after like 20 minutes passed, Mr. Hoover walked to go find a pay phone. He came back around 5:30 and he told us his wife was coming to get us. She got there around 6 and we didn't get to the Joy Hall until 6:30 and man were we hungry!!! so we ate and did all that good stuff and i came home!!

okay..most people who know me and Ashley, can picture this in the future. I don't know how we got talking about this during lunch today but, that's okay! Picture this: Our Senior year of high school, Ashley being COMPLETELY wasted, her head over a toilet, and me holding her hair out of her face! And then Amber Gilson standing 5 feet away from us saying "HA! I told you not to drink too much!!" lol! oh my, me and my friends seriously have some good memories together!! geez, don't get any bad ideas about Ashley before ya get to know her though!!!

well, just in English, on the computer, OBVIOUSLY! just bored!! doing my homework for social studies for 7th period. haha! maybe i should of just stayed home today!! Cuz Jamie's mommy can't pick us up from youth group tonight so, we're not going. :( this sucks majorly man!! then again, something might pop up that some one will give me a ride, who knows!! Hopefully that's what happens! If not, it will give me a night to catch up with homework. But seriously, I really wanna see Andrew! I really wanna live in Warren but, like i tell everyone, i really can't see myself living anywhere but Youngsville until i graduate! Until then, i'm stuck here. Zack says he hates Warren, i told him i would love to trade him places! Youngsville is just too boring for me sumtimes. When you can't drive or go anywhere, it's really boring here. Cuz the only thing you CAN do is walk around town(kiley-with our wonderful heart-to-heart walks!). I can't wait until my Junior year! Seriously...A LOT is happening to me that year. Me and my friends getting our lisences, me getting my Junior jacket, me going to Ireland...it goes on and on!

well, still sick, stuck at school. oh well, only a half hour to go! A lot on my mind i didn't get to say this morning. Well, my friend from Warren, Zack, really has been ticking me off! He keeps lying about stupid crap that he really has no point in saying. That's like a MAJOR thing i hate-lyers! they make me mad! it's just like, dude, why can't you just tell the freakin truth? AHH!! Just too many things bothering me lately. I guess it's the little things that i don't confront and then they just start to add up and...all the frustration is coming out now. It's just crazy. Well, Bill Bunce is home from the Marines. I don't know when he came home, when he's leaving...all i know is that he is home for 10 days and then when he leaves, he's being based in South Carolina. That's a good thing. On Saturday, i was on the computer at home, and i hear someone come in the front door, it was Sam Huff. Then i went to give her a hug, then i look and THERE'S BILL! My jaw DROPPED! I didn't know he was comin home, geez, why can't people inform me on these things??!! But, that was like the highlight of my weekend. Only 29 more days of school left!! YEAH, ROCK ON!!! I can't wait till summer. Just no stress, no worries...none of that crap!! This summer-all that i have is...going up to the pool, YAC, going up to the pool some more, then camp li-lo-li (maybe), fair, band camp. i can't wait!! besides the band camp part!!! lol!! oh yeah, Miss Welsh's class fishy Woody died...i really don't care!! Jamie was happy about it...why, i wish i knew!! But as far as i know, me and Jamie are going up to youth group tomorrow-really can't wait!!!<3

Man, this weekend went by REALLY fast. Friday and Saturday Jamie stayed here. We had a lot of fun, man!! Then yesterday, i did absolutely nothing other than talk on here, watch tv, and did homework. I seriously hate homework!! It's a waste of my time! i wish i had a study hall. but, with my shedule and everything, i won't have one until my Sophmore year. ANYWAYZ, my friend from Warren likes Jamie. They just met last Tuesday at youth group. It's crazy! But, who knows whats gonna happen between them. But, Jamie got me sick!! i SHOULD be staying home from school but, with tomorrow being Tuesday and i barely have enough time to do my homework for that day, it would be worse if i had to do today's work also.

well, i'm supposed to be gettin ready for school but, i wanted to write in here first. last night, went up to Warren again for youth group, but this time with Jamie! it was great! i really wanted her to meet Andrew!!! but, none of us knew this before we got to the church but, we had a lil cook out thing last night. it was great!! i'm seriously happy that Andrew and Jamie got to meet each other. I mean, my other 3 best friends got to meet him, it was time for her to meet him too. but, she was the first ones outta my friends to meet Lacey and Tony. lol. Jamie was mad cuz Jayda got to meet Andrew before her. it wasn't my fault! lol. i had NO clue that Jayda was goin up to Stateline on Saturday until i saw her. i told her that morning that i was going with Andrew so, she knew i was gonna be with him.........

man...yesterday WAS SO awesome! well, i set my alarm to go off at 9 but, i woke up at 8 and after that i couldn't fall back asleep. i got up and got on here for like a half hour. then i went upstairs, took a bath and did my hair. by that time it was 10 and Andrew called me and we got everything worked out with what was going on yesterday. Then at 11:30 Tammy came to my house and her dad took us up to Bilo to do tag days for band. we worked from 12-3. i was counting down the minutes until 3 came!....finally 3 o' clock came and Andrew and his step mom came and picked me up. Then we went and picked up Adam then went to Andrew's house. We went outside and played on his trampoline-it was fun!! then we went inside and watched tv for a lil while. then we had a lil dinner-peanut butter & jelly sandwiches. Then we left his house and went and picked up Adam and Andrew's friend Alissa (i think thats how ya spell it). then we headed up for Stateline!! The races were A LOT of fun!!! i was sitting there, eating my fries, and i hear "there she is!"-i look up and its Jayda and her mom Connie. i jumped up and gave Jayda a hug-Andrew had NO clue who it was and he looked at me like i had lost it. so, we hung out with the 5 of us. man, i had A LOT of fun! it was great!! i hope that i get to go with Andrew next time he goes up there!!

last night-went up to Warren for youth group!!! oh my, i had a kinda down day cuz i really had nothing to look forward to, except jazz band, cuz i didn't know i was going to youth group. Well, i got home from jazz at 5:40. I walk in the front door, grab the phone, look to see if Andrew called me, he did, so, i called him back. He was at Perkins (great place, right Niki?), in the middle of getting his food ordered, and i asked him why he called. He was like "well-my step-mom was in Youngsville and she was gonna pick you up and bring you here, but you weren't home." well, we got off the phone after saying good-bye, and then he calls me 3 minutes later and says "do you have a ride up to Warren? my dad said he would take you home." i SPRINT to my living room and jump on the couch and ask my dad if he can give me a ride, and obviously he did. so, i made dinner, ate, got outta there, went to youth group. the service was great, like it was last week. after the service, we sat on the stairs in the church then decided to go outside. we were standing outside and we decided to play hide and seek. Andrew GRABS my arm and pulls me and starts running and we went and hid. it wasn't a GREAT hiding place but, it was the only one we could find at the time! then somehow all of us ended up on South Street and we went to south street school and played on the playground. it was fun. Andrew. Amanda, and Allura (i think that's all who it was) were having fun going down memory lane walking around the school, i kinda felt left out, obviously. Lacey and Tony, were on the playground still at the time. Zac was with us, i kept going in and out of transes and my LALA land so, i wasn't paying much attention. then all of a sudden 8:45 comes around and we headed over back to the church. wow-great times. like i said last week, this week would be better for me not being shy! haha! i'm pretty sure what we did yesterday is what we're gonna be doing next week, about getting me there and back. who knows. i'll have to talk to Andrew about it!

But wow-i can't believe Andrew's dad gave me a ride home. i was REALLY REALLY REALLY glad too! i love being with Andrew. i also like being with his friends. they're fun to hang with. i don't know them that well but-still, they're fun to hang with. i SUCK at learning SOOOOO many new names all in one night-i couldn't remember everyone's name last week! this week was better though.

i'm starting to like this class. but, i'm still gonna say it's POINT LESS!!!!!!!! it drives me nuts. i like the teacher and everything it's just that, i already know how to use a computer, why do i have to take a class about it?? it's all just review. then next year, i have to take this class again. it's just the same class with a different name. but, J. Lewis is home for the week so, tomorrow, as far as i know, i can't go to youth group. i REALLY REALLY REALLY REALLY wanted to go!!! but i'm SO sad that i can't. Well, tomorrrow Spinney's gonna be with J. Lewis so, that's why he's not gonna be able to pick me up, but it's understandable....Well, my parents are gonna be at a dart banquet and my sister is babysitting all at the same time tonight so, i'll be online all night. go figure, Danielle, being alone, again.
